<subSubSection pageId="267" pageNumber="268" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="267.[151,1436,618,1185]" pageId="267" pageNumber="268">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[265,496,942,969]" pageId="267" pageNumber="268" refId="ref368401" refString="Rondani, C. (1857) Dipterologiae italicae prodromus. Vol: II. Species italicae ordinis dipterorum in genera characteribus definita, ordinatim collectae, methodo analitica distinctae, et novis vel minus cognitis descriptis. Pars prima. Oestridae: Syrphfidae [sic!]: Conopidae. A. Stocchi, Parmae [= Parma], 264 pp., 1 pl. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8160" type="book" year="1857">Rondani (1857: 114)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[615,883,942,968]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphaerophoria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="267" pageNumber="268" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oleandri">
<emphasis box="[615,883,942,968]" italics="true" pageId="267" pageNumber="268">Sphaerophoria oleandri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from a single male: “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="267" pageNumber="268">unico exemplare masculo … invento a Doct. Schembri</emphasis>
[single male specimen]”, received from Schembri, to whom he attributed the species name. 
<bibRefCitation author="Vockeroth, J. R." box="[274,543,1014,1041]" pageId="267" pageNumber="268" pagination="1627 - 1635" refId="ref377069" refString="Vockeroth, J. R. (1971) The identity of some Holarctic and Old World species of Sphaerophoria (Diptera: Syrphidae). The Canadian Entomologist, 103 (11), 1627 - 1635. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / Ent 1031627 - 11" type="journal article" year="1971">Vockeroth (1971: 1632)</bibRefCitation>
incorrectly designated one of the two MZUF males as the 
<typeStatus box="[1212,1318,1014,1040]" pageId="267" pageNumber="268">lectotype</typeStatus>
. There are 
<specimenCount box="[199,312,1050,1077]" pageId="267" pageNumber="268" type="male">two males</specimenCount>
in the MZUF without any label indicating their type status. We are unable to single out the male upon which Rondani based his description. We leave the recognition of the 
<typeStatus box="[994,1092,1086,1112]" pageId="267" pageNumber="268">holotype</typeStatus>
to a future specialist. There is a MZUF specimen (Box A) from “Insubria” [= 
<collectingRegion box="[732,852,1122,1149]" country="Italy" name="Lombardia" pageId="267" pageNumber="268">Lombardy</collectingRegion>
] and a MSNC male from “ 
<taxonomicName box="[1152,1231,1122,1148]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pomacentridae" genus="Parma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="267" pageNumber="268" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Parma</taxonomicName>
”, neither of which are from the type locality.
</paragraph>
